------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party data sources
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Meridian ingests and re-processes public trade statistics from the
following sources. Each export bundle written by Meridian carries the
specific source URLs for the releases it draws on (see "Sources
appendix" in `03_Findings.md` and the per-finding files under
`provenance/`). The summary below records the licensing posture for
each source.

1. Eurostat (European Statistical Office) — Comext bulk files

   Re-use of Eurostat statistical data is permitted under European
   Commission Decision 2011/833/EU of 12 December 2011 on the reuse of
   Commission documents, subject to acknowledgement of the source.

   Suggested attribution in derived journalism:
     "Source: Eurostat (Comext)"

   https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/about/policies/copyright

2. HM Revenue & Customs (UK) — Overseas Trade Statistics (uktradeinfo)

   HMRC OTS data is published under the Open Government Licence v3.0
   (OGL v3.0). Re-use is permitted with attribution.

   Required attribution:
     "Contains HMRC data licensed under the Open Government Licence
      v3.0."

   https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/doc/open-government-licence/version/3/
   https://www.uktradeinfo.com/

3. General Administration of Customs of the People's Republic of China
   (GACC) — monthly statistical releases

   GACC publishes Chinese customs trade statistics on its public
   website (english.customs.gov.cn). The releases are official
   government statistical publications. Meridian fetches the
   HTML/XLS release pages, preserves the original source URLs in
   the database, and attributes them in every export.

   Suggested attribution in derived journalism:
     "Source: General Administration of Customs of the People's
      Republic of China (GACC)"

   https://english.customs.gov.cn/

4. European Central Bank — euro reference exchange rates

   ECB statistical data is © European Central Bank. Reproduction is
   authorised provided the source is acknowledged. Meridian fetches
   end-of-month CNY/EUR, USD/EUR and GBP/EUR rates via the ECB SDW
   API and uses them for currency conversion in cross-source
   comparisons.

   Required attribution:
     "Exchange rates: European Central Bank"

   https://www.ecb.europa.eu/services/disclaimer/html/index.en.html

